<section class="section">
  <div class="container faq-stage">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 class="section-title section-title-glow">Career coaching cost — what to know before you invest</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>How much does career coaching cost on average?</h3>
        <p>Career coaching costs range from $150–$400/hour for session-based coaching to $2,000–$15,000 for full-service packages. For mid-to-senior professionals targeting $100K–$350K roles, expect quality full-service coaching to cost $3,000–$8,000 depending on scope and coach expertise.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>Is career coaching tax deductible?</h3>
        <p>Career coaching costs may be deductible as a job search expense if you are looking for a job in your current field. Consult your tax advisor — the rules vary depending on your employment status and the coaching purpose. This is a question your CPA can answer with certainty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>Is career coaching worth the cost?</h3>
        <p>For professionals targeting roles $40K–$100K above their current compensation, the ROI on quality career coaching is typically 5–15x in the first year. The cost question dissolves when you frame it as: how much am I leaving on the table every month I spend searching without a clear system?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>What is the cheapest way to get career coaching?</h3>
        <p>Free resources — this blog, salary guides, interview guides — cover a significant amount of what you need. If your situation is relatively straightforward (clear target, recent active search, just need execution support), starting with free resources is smart. If you are stuck, the free resources have not moved the needle, and the roles you are targeting are worth $100K+, investing in coaching makes financial sense.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>How do I know if a career coach is worth their price?</h3>
        <p>Ask three questions: (1) What percentage of your clients land offers within 60–90 days? (2) Can you share specific client outcomes — role level, salary increase, timeline? (3) Do you have hiring-side experience in my industry? A coach who cannot answer these questions clearly is not worth their price.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-card">
        <h3>Does Askia offer payment plans for career coaching?</h3>
        <p>Book a strategy call to discuss options. We work with clients to find the right structure given their situation and timeline.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

